indicator.name: KPI Name
indicator.rangeOfLongTimeIntervalDis: Range of longitudinal time interval distance
indicator.defaultAsTheScenarioEndCondition: Default as the scenario end condition
indicator.kpi0-name: Number of times the time-to-collision is too small
indicator.kpi0-def: Number of times it takes less than the time-to-collision threshold to collide with a traffic vehicle
indicator.kpi0-calc: If the time spent colliding with the traffic vehicle is less than the time-to-collision threshold when ego vehicle runs at the current speed, it is counted as one time
indicator.kpi1-name: Number of times the car-following distance is too small
indicator.kpi1-def: Number of times the distance from traffic vehicles is less than the threshold
indicator.kpi1-calc: When the lateral and longitudinal distance between the ego vehicle and the traffic vehicle is less than the threshold, it is recorded as one time
indicator.kpi2-name: Number of times acceleration is too large
indicator.kpi2-def: Number of times longitudinal acceleration is too large
indicator.kpi2-calc: Determine the number of times longitudinal acceleration of the ego vehicle exceeds its positive threshold according to the continuous frame sequence data. Continuous exceeding behavior is recorded as one time
indicator.kpi3-name: Number of times deceleration is too large
indicator.kpi3-def: Number of times longitudinal braking is excessive
indicator.kpi3-calc: Determine the number of times longitudinal acceleration of the ego vehicle exceeds its negative threshold according to the continuous frame sequence data. Continuous exceeding behavior is recorded as one time
indicator.kpi4-name: Number of times lateral acceleration is too large
indicator.kpi4-def: Number of times lateral steering is excessive
indicator.kpi4-calc: Determine the number of times yaw acceleration of the ego vehicle exceeds its positive threshold according to the continuous frame sequence data. Continuous exceeding behavior is recorded as one time
indicator.kpi5-def: Times of exceeding the road speed limit
indicator.kpi5-calc: Determine the number of times speed of the ego vehicle exceeds the road speed limit according to the continuous frame sequence data. Continuous exceeding behavior is recorded as one time
indicator.kpi7-name: Times of driving over the solid line
indicator.kpi7-def: Number of times the wheel touches the solid line of the road
indicator.kpi7-calc: Whether the wheel of the ego vehicle overlaps with the solid line
indicator.kpi8-def: Number of times the signal light is red when the ego vehicle passes through the intersection
indicator.kpi8-calc: When the intersection is red and the ego vehicle continuously appears outside the parking line, it is counted as one time
indicator.kpi9-name: Whether ego vehicle reached the end point
indicator.kpi9-def: Whether the ego vehicle has reached the destination
indicator.kpi9-calc: Whether the distance from the end point is less than the threshold, and whether the speed is zero when it is less than the threshold
indicator.kpi10-name: Whether customer customization has reached the end
indicator.kpi10-def: Whether the ego vehicle has reached the destination
indicator.kpi10-calc: Whether the distance from the end point is less than the threshold, and whether the speed is zero when it is less than the threshold
indicator.kpi11-name: Number of times the lateral offset distance is too large
indicator.kpi11-def: Comparison of absolute value and threshold value of lateral offset of planned path
indicator.kpi11-calc: Number of times the lateral offset from a given trajectory is greater than the threshold
indicator.kpi12-name: Maximum lateral offset to the left
indicator.kpi12-def: Maximum lateral offset to the left after trajectory planning
indicator.kpi12-calc: Maximum lateral offset from a given track
indicator.kpi13-name: Maximum lateral offset to the right
indicator.kpi13-def: Maximum lateral offset to the right after trajectory planning
indicator.kpi13-calc: Maximum lateral offset from a given track
indicator.kpi14-def: The lateral offset value of the planned path and the average value of the left and right offsets
indicator.kpi14-calc: Arithmetic mean of left and right offset
indicator.kpi15-name: User-defined lateral offset is too large
indicator.kpi15-def: By comparing the absolute value of lateral offset of the planned path with the threshold value
indicator.kpi15-calc: Number of times the lateral offset from a given trajectory is greater than the threshold
indicator.kpi16-def: Whether the maximum running time of the scenario is exceeded
indicator.kpi16-calc: Comparison between cumulative running time and maximum duration threshold
indicator.becauseThisKpi: Because this kpi {n}, scene is over
